-- China Issues Flood Warning Before Yangtze Peaks, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2012-07-23T18:44:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-23/china-issues-flood-warning-before-yangtze-peaks-xinhua-reports.html
China’s State Flood Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters said it started a level-II emergency
response to flooding, the second-most severe of five warning
levels, to prepare for surging water flows down the  Yangtze
river  and nationwide floods, Xinhua News Agency reported.  The Three Gorges Dam will have its largest flood peak this
year today, with maximum flow of 70,000 cubic meters of water a
second, the official news service reported. Water levels in in
the river’s upper reaches are “exceedingly high,” it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  